CatDescriptText: image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 13, 1959, pg. A16, reads: "Anyone For Dimples? - Gloria Sweeney shows her dimples as she models a hat and dress for the D.I. show."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Gloria Sweeney wearing light colored dress with short sleeves, belt, and light colored hat with ribbon, seated in upholstered chair with fringe in home of Gloria Grate in preparation for D.I.'s "Atlantic City U.S.A" revue held in the Press Room of the Hotel Sherwyn
